
To install it do the following:

1) Start Karaf shell
<Karaf bin dir>/karaf 

2) Install the OSGi Services as Karaf Features

features:addurl mvn:org.jbehave.osgi/jbehave-osgi-features/1.0-SNAPSHOT/xml/karaf
features:install jbehave-osgi  

<-- Fails with error -->
karaf@root> Exception in thread "Thread-18" java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Cannot write resource: org/xmlpull/mxp1/MXParser.class :43114: exception: java.io.IOException: Pipe closed
        at aQute.lib.osgi.Jar.writeResource(Jar.java:302)
        at aQute.lib.osgi.Jar.write(Jar.java:211)
        at org.ops4j.pax.swissbox.bnd.BndUtils$1.run(BndUtils.java:174)
        
3) After installing it you can test with the command:

jbehave:status

4) Install the bundles with the Embedder <-- not working yet -->

osgi:install mvn:org.jbehave.osgi/jbehave-osgi-services/1.0-SNAPSHOT/jar
osgi:install mvn:org.jbehave.osgi/jbehave-osgi-commands/1.0-SNAPSHOT/jar

5) Run the embeddables via the Embedder

jbehave:runAsEmbeddables
